===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
# A West Germanic, or more specifically High German, language that developed from [[Middle High German]] dialects, with an admixture of vocabulary from multiple source languages including Hebrew-Aramaic, Romance, Slavic, English, etc., and mostly written in [[Hebrew]] characters which is used mainly among [[Ashkenazi]]c [[Jew]]s from central and eastern Europe.
#* '''1983''', Philip Baldi, ''An Introduction to the Indo-European Languages'', p. 128:
#*: '''Yiddish''' is a High German language [...] two varieties of Yiddish developed [...]
